text: The 1990–91 Combined Counties Football League season was the 13th in the history of the Combined Counties Football League, a football competition in England. The league was won by Farnham Town for the first time. There was no promotion this season. ==Clubs== The league was reduced to 17 clubs from 18 after Cove were promoted to the Isthmian League, and Weybridge Town and Chobham left the league. Two new clubs joined: *Ashford Town, joining from the Surrey Premier League. *Sandhurst Town, joining from the Chiltonian League. ===League table=== ==References== ==External links== * Combined Counties League Official Site 1990-91 Category:1990–91 in English football leagues
